quits <- fredr(series_id = "JTSQUL",
                       observation_start = as.Date("2000-12-01"),
                       observation_end = as.Date("2023-12-01")) %>%
  dplyr::select(date, series_id, value) %>%
  mutate(quits_first_diff = value - lag(value),
         quits_second_diff = difference(value, differences = 2)) %>%
  tsibble(index = date)
quits$quits <- quits$value

emp_fam <- fredr(series_id = "LNU04000313",
                       observation_start = as.Date("2000-12-01"),
                       observation_end = as.Date("2023-12-01")) %>%
  dplyr::select(date, series_id, value) %>%
  mutate(unemp_first_diff = value - lag(value),
         unemp_second_diff = difference(value, differences = 2)) %>%
  tsibble(index = date)

emp_fam$emp_fam <- emp_fam$value
fed_funds <- fredr(series_id = "FEDFUNDS",
                       observation_start = as.Date("2000-12-01"),
                       observation_end = as.Date("2023-12-01")) %>%
  dplyr::select(date, series_id, value) %>%
  mutate(fed_first_diff = value - lag(value),
         fed_second_diff = difference(value, differences = 2)) %>%
  tsibble(index = date)
fed_funds$fed_funds <- fed_funds$value

eggs <- fredr(series_id = "APU0000708111",
                       observation_start = as.Date("2000-12-01"),
                       observation_end = as.Date("2023-12-01")) %>%
  dplyr::select(date, series_id, value) %>%
  mutate(egg_first_diff = value - lag(value),
         egg_second_diff = difference(value, differences = 2)) %>%
  tsibble(index = date)

eggs$eggs <- eggs$value


comb <- cbind.data.frame(eggs, emp_fam, fed_funds, quits)
comb <- subset(comb, select = c(eggs, emp_fam,fed_funds,quits,date))
jo <- subset(comb, select = c(eggs, emp_fam,fed_funds,quits))
joh_test <- ca.jo(jo)
summary(joh_test)

Question 3

train_comb <- comb[1:267, ]

#doing an extra value here so when we difference there are still 10
test_comb <- comb[267:277, ]

test_comb_diff <- test_comb %>%
  dplyr::select(emp_fam, fed_funds, quits, eggs) %>%
  mutate(diff_emp = difference(emp_fam),
         diff_FF = difference(fed_funds),
         diff_quits = difference(log(quits)),
         diff_eggs = difference(log(eggs))) %>%
  filter(complete.cases(.))

endogenous_vars <- train_comb %>%
  dplyr::select(emp_fam, fed_funds, quits, eggs) %>%
  mutate(diff_emp = difference(log(emp_fam)),
         diff_FF = difference(log(fed_funds)),
         diff_quits = difference(log(quits)),
         diff_eggs = difference(log(eggs))) %>%
  filter(complete.cases(.))


endogenous_vars <- endogenous_vars %>%
  as_tibble(.) %>%
  dplyr::select(-emp_fam, -fed_funds, -quits,-eggs) %>%
  as.matrix(.)


  

var_model <- VAR(endogenous_vars, p=2,type="const", ic = "AIC", lag.max = 5,)

summary(var_model)

Question 4

# Add seasonal terms
var_model_seasonal <- VAR(endogenous_vars, p = 2, type = "both", ic = "AIC", season = list(4),lag.max = 5,)

# Add a trend term and more lags
var_model_trend_lags <- VAR(endogenous_vars, p = 3, type = "trend", ic = "AIC", lag.max = 5,)

forecast_1 <- predict(var_model, n.ahead = 10)
forecast_2 <- predict(var_model_seasonal, n.ahead = 10)
forecast_3 <- predict(var_model_trend_lags, n.ahead = 10)

Graphs

#loss functions

# Define a function to calculate loss functions
calculate_loss <- function(forecast, actual) {
  mae <- mean(abs(forecast - actual))
  mse <- mean((forecast - actual)^2)
  rmse <- sqrt(mse)
  return(list(MAE = mae, MSE = mse, RMSE = rmse))
}

# Calculate loss functions for forecast_1
loss_forecast_1 <- lapply(names(forecast_1$fcst), function(variable) {
  calculate_loss(forecast_1$fcst[[variable]], test_comb_diff[, variable])
})

# Calculate loss functions for forecast_2
loss_forecast_2 <- lapply(names(forecast_2$fcst), function(variable) {
  calculate_loss(forecast_2$fcst[[variable]], test_comb_diff[, variable])
})

# Calculate loss functions for forecast_3
loss_forecast_3 <- lapply(names(forecast_3$fcst), function(variable) {
  calculate_loss(forecast_3$fcst[[variable]], test_comb_diff[, variable])
})

  cat("MSE:", loss_forecast_1[[i]]$MSE, "\n")
  cat("RMSE:", loss_forecast_1[[i]]$RMSE, "\n")
}
